 optimizing the `smartNull.name()` method? I should inspect the Mockito invocation's `toString` for mock name defaults; they aren't necessary but would be safer with `hasMessageContaining(\\\"findEntity\\\")`. Lastly, I might need to use the concrete class `Entity` with a non-final method to enhance compatibility.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class structure**\\n\\nI’m thinking about whether to choose a class instead of an interface for the Repository. Initially, I had a mock with a subclass of the interface, which seems fine. Maybe I should edit the nested Entity to a public static class. Since interface methods are implicitly public, I could go with `public interface Repository` and `public static class Entity`. I also wonder if Checkstyle prefers inner classes to come after methods, but that doesn’t seem to be required here. I'll go ahead and edit the message.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_beMQ8Bb2NLqoygfdOB9nB90E|fc_09693a7b58e56e42016a21f5458c38819383939f974d85819d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ReturnsSmartNullsInnerThrowsSmartNullPointerTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    interface Repository {\n        Entity findEntity();\n    }\n\n    interface Entity {\n        String name();\n    }\n", "newText": "    public interface Repository {\n        Entity findEntity();\n    }\n\n    public static class Entity {\n        public String name() {\n            return \"entity\";\n        }\n    }\n"}, {"oldText": "                .hasMessageContaining(\"You have a NullPointerException here\")\n                .hasMessageContaining(\"repository.findEntity()\");\n", "newText": "                .hasMessageContaining(\"You have a NullPointerException here\")\n                .hasMessageContaining(\"findEntity\");\n"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ReturnsSmartNullsI